\tan x+\tan^2 x+\tan^3 x=1
2\cos^6 x-2\cos^4 x+\cos^2 x
\tan x(1+\tan^2x)=1-\tan^2x\iff\tan x=\frac{1-\tan^2x}{1+\tan^2x}=\cos2x
2\cos^6x-2\cos^4x+\cos^2x=\frac{\cos^2x}2\left[4\cos^4x-4\cos^2x+2\right]
=\frac{\cos^2x\left[(2\cos^2x-1)^2+1\right]}2
=\frac{\cos^2x\left[\cos^22x+1\right]}2=\cdots
\displaystyle\tan x(1+\tan^2x)=1-\tan^2x
\displaystyle\implies\sin x=(\cos^2x-\sin^2x)\cos x=\{\cos^2x-(1-\cos^2x)\}\cos x=2\cos^3x-\cos x
\displaystyle\implies(2\cos^3x-\cos x)^2=\sin^2x=1-\cos^2x
\displaystyle\implies2(2\cos^6x-2\cos^4x+\cos^2x)=1
